  "internal_thinking": "My starting settlement is at Node 20, providing W11, B6, S8. I need to place a road adjacent to Node 20. The available neighbors are 19, 21, and 10. I analyzed each option for immediate resource gain and long-term strategic potential, considering future settlement locations and access to ports. \n\nPlacing a road from 20 to 19 would connect to Hex 8 (B10), giving me two Brick hexes (B6, B10), W11, and S8. This is decent for road building but doesn't offer diverse new resources or a port access point. \n\nPlacing a road from 20 to 21 would not connect to any new hexes immediately. This path leads towards Node 22 (H10-Desert, H6-W3, H5-B6). If I settled at Node 22, I would gain W3, resulting in two Wood (W11, W3), two Brick (B6), and one Sheep (S8). While this is a good resource mix for building, Node 22 is adjacent to the Desert, making it a less desirable settlement location.\n\nPlacing a road from 20 to 10 immediately connects to Hex 1 (W12), adding a second Wood hex to my production (W11, W12, B6, S8). This path leads towards Node 11 (H5-B6, H2-S5, H1-W12). A settlement at Node 11 would provide S5 and W12. Combined with Node 20, I would have a balanced production of 2x Wood (W11, W12), 1x Brick (B6), and 2x Sheep (S8, S5), with good numbers (11, 12, 6, 8, 5). Crucially, Node 11 is adjacent to Node 3, which is a Wheat 2:1 port. Gaining access to a specific 2:1 port, especially for Wheat, is a significant strategic advantage for future development cards and cities, even if I don't produce Wheat directly yet. This option offers the best balance of immediate resource gain and long-term strategic potential for expansion and trade. Therefore, the road between 20 and 10 is the optimal choice.",
